extends ../../layout

block vars
  - const title = 'The tenth Workshop of SIGPX';
  - const path = 'en/10';

block description
  p SIGPX is a Japanese domestic study group for those interested in programming environments and their programming experience, founded in January 2016. We gather for exchanging information on state-of-the-art research and development projects relevant to programming experience. This page shows the overview of its tenth workshop.

block body
  section#overview
    h2 Overview
    p
      a(href='https://prg.is.titech.ac.jp/en/people/cong/') Youyou Cong
      |  and 
      a(href='https://junkato.jp') Jun Kato
      |  reported their Dagstuhl Seminar experiences (
      a(href='https://www.dagstuhl.de/en/program/calendar/semhp/?semnr=22302') #22302
      | , 
      a(href='https://www.dagstuhl.de/en/program/calendar/semhp/?semnr=22231') #22231
      | ). Additionally, researchers shared their recent research outcomes.
    p
      | We are using 
      a(href='https://sigpx.slack.com') the Slack team
      |  and Google Docs for fostering discussions during and even after the event. Let 
      a#apply-mail(href) me
      |  know if you are interested in participation, though the primary language is Japanese.
    ul
      li
        strong Location:
        |  Online
      li
        strong Date:
        |  12/22/2022 (Wed) 13:30-16:00
      li
        strong Topics:
        |  "Dagstuhl Seminar reports" and "recent research outcomes"
      li
        a(href='https://sigpx.slack.com/messages/sigpx10/') Slack channel #sigpx10
